page.title: 04FLORA OF THE FEN EDGE
page.content: A survey of plants along a 200 metre section of Street Way was carried out. Street Way was originally a track across the open downland which became fenced as part of the Parliamentary Enclosure of the late eighteenth century. {PLANTS FOUND {Hedges Dog Rose, Hawthorn {Plants White Campion, Scabious, Buttercup, Poppy, Dock, White Clover, Wild Parsnip, Speedwell, Black Medick, Dead Nettle, Groundsel, Greater Burnet Saxifrage, Greater Knapweed, Hedge Bindweed, Chamomile, Scotch Thistle, Plantain, Stinging Nettle, Purple Clover, Mignonette, Vetch, Blackberry, Dropwort, zShepherds Purse
